  "why": "The paper provides empirical, diagnostic insight that links discovered failures to statistical properties of the model’s behaviour (distribution differences measured by MMD on the logits layer) and shows correlations between those statistical patterns and defenses' detection success. The method explicitly measures distribution difference (DF / MMD) between test suites and other classes and demonstrates (with plots and experiments) that as MMD_target decreases the error rate and the ability to bypass detectors increase. However, the paper does not go further to explain deeper root causes such as reliance on specific spurious or non-robust features, label noise, or overfitting mechanisms — i.e., it provides statistical/internal-signal based diagnostics but not explanations tying failures to concrete model vulnerabilities at feature or dataset-causal level. This corresponds to the metric’s “Medium” level: partial diagnostic insight via model internals/statistical failure patterns but not full causal explanations of underlying vulnerabilities.",
